premise_source_doc_sentence: Murry Gage Wilson  (  July 2 , 1917 -- June 4 , 1973  )  was an American musician , record producer , and businessman who acted as the first manager of the Beach Boys , a rock band formed by his sons Brian , Dennis , and Carl Wilson , his nephew Mike Love , and their friend Al Jardine .
For most of the 1960s , Murry also worked as a music publisher for the band .
After the Beach Boys dismissed Murry as their manager in 1964 , he produced the sound-alike group the Sunrays , and recorded a single solo album : The Many Moods of Murry Wilson  (  1967  )  .
In 1969 , without any of the Beach Boys ' knowledge or consent , Wilson sold off their publishing company Sea of Tunes for $ 700,000  (  equivalent to $ in  )  , then considered a paltry sum .
In 1973 , he died aged 55 of a heart attack .
The Many Moods of Murry Wilson is the sole album release by Murry Wilson , the father of Brian , Carl and Dennis Wilson and uncle of Mike Love of The Beach Boys .
His name is incorrectly spelled on the Stanley Cup for the 1973 , 1976 , and 1977 Montreal Canadiens .
Murray Charles Wilson  (  born November 7 , 1951 in Toronto , Ontario and raised in Ottawa , Ontario  )  is a retired Canadian ice hockey forward .
